Acer, Fubon Financial, Polaris Securities: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-24T00:22:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/acer-fubon-financial-polaris-securities-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index rose 37.04, or 0.4 percent, to 8,545.08.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT): The world’s second-largest computer
maker is cutting the number of employees in  China  by about 10
percent, the China Business News reported, citing an
unidentified person familiar with the situation. More than 100
employees were cut, the report said. Most of them were former
workers from Founder Technology Group Corp. after Acer took over
management of Founder Technology’s branded computer business,
the report said. The stock advanced 4.8 percent to NT$71.50.  Fubon Financial Holding Co. (2881 TT): Fubon Securities
Investment Trust Co. was granted a $100 million quota to invest
in yuan-denominated shares and bonds by China’s foreign exchange
regulator, parent Fubon Financial said in an e-mail statement
yesterday. The stock gained 1.3 percent to NT$38.30.  Polaris Securities Co. (2854 TT): The company may merge
with  China Development Financial Holding Corp. (2883) ’s (2883 TT) Grand
Cathay Securities Corp. unit in a share swap, the Economic Daily
News reported, without saying where it got the information.
Polaris Securities will become a unit of China Development
Financial after the transaction, the newspaper said. Polaris
increased 0.5 percent to NT$19.05. China Development surged 0.4
percent to NT$11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
